1/ create a folder for the components that has a capitol letter
2/ use functional compoennts unless you are defning a state
3/ use the word "props" for passing data to components from parent
4/ end method with word "handler" if it is hanlding an event
5/ Create folder for component that starts with capitolr letter
6/ capitolize first letter of file name for component files:
Person.js in the "Person" folder
7/ pass objects as props instead of primitives
// Don't pass primatives
<UserAccount
  name={user.name}
  email={user.email}
  id={user.id}
/>

// Pass objects
<UserAccount user={user} />

8/ short circuit and destructue (see files 11 and 12)
